div.span: SSL certificate is produced in ‘Certificate Manager’ (for a TLD acquired either by Route53 or a 3rd party domain registrar). SSL certificate is attached to the CloudFront distribution, enabling HTTPS. A Route53 Public Hosted Zone provides DNS, resolving host name in users browser to the CloudFront Distribution.
[OPTIONAL] - WAF is configured to serve as an intermediary between (user) <—> (cloudfront) in order to monitor/control malicious traffic.
